  "text": "In a comparable study, [CITATION_1] investigated cichlid communities in Lake Tanganyika. Interestingly, the individual importance of the assembly processes inferred is very similar to ours, with dispersal limitation being the dominant process. In contrast to our study, they did not find a correlation of process importance with environmental characteristics. The reasons for this difference remain unclear, though differences in the life history of the study taxa and in the spatial extant of the study area [CITATION_2] performed a local study) may play a role.",
